WEBVTT

00:03.758 --> 00:04.931
- Private Petrocelli,
step away from the goat bomb!

00:05.034 --> 00:06.241
- It's not a bomb.

00:06.344 --> 00:07.793
- Yeah, that's what
they want you to think.

00:07.896 --> 00:09.275
Now move
so I can engage the threat.

00:09.379 --> 00:12.517
- Buckley's spirit
is in this goat.

00:12.620 --> 00:14.379
- You're fucking crazy.

00:14.482 --> 00:16.206
- I am not moving.

00:16.310 --> 00:17.275
- Yeah, well
I ain't getting blown up

00:17.379 --> 00:19.448
by no goddamn suicide goat,
either.

00:19.551 --> 00:22.000
- It's not a suicide goat.

00:22.103 --> 00:23.793
[tense music]

00:23.896 --> 00:25.827
Don't worry, Boz.

00:25.931 --> 00:27.172
I'm not gonna let anything
happen to you.

00:27.275 --> 00:29.103
- Hey, what are you saying
to it?

00:29.206 --> 00:30.724
- That is none
of your business.

00:30.827 --> 00:31.551
- Some sort of code?

00:31.655 --> 00:33.344
- To a goat?
- [bleats]

00:33.448 --> 00:35.827
- It's not a bomb;
it's a fucking goat.

00:35.931 --> 00:37.896
It's my associate's fingers
in its belly.

00:38.000 --> 00:39.241
- [bleats]

00:39.344 --> 00:40.551
- Gnarly.

00:40.655 --> 00:41.586
- Yeah, and now I gotta
cut that goat open.

00:41.689 --> 00:43.551
And that annoying
little shit there

00:43.655 --> 00:44.724
isn't gonna move to the side

00:44.827 --> 00:45.724
unless you put
your fucking weapon down.

00:45.827 --> 00:47.517
- Well, we don't
take orders from you.

00:47.620 --> 00:49.241
- But you do take
orders from me.

00:49.344 --> 00:50.689
And put that knife away.

00:50.793 --> 00:52.379
Nobody's cuttin'
this poor little animal open.

00:52.482 --> 00:55.379
That's the cutest fuckin' goat
I've ever seen.

00:55.482 --> 00:57.000
Ain't that
the cutest fuckin' goat

00:57.103 --> 00:57.965
you've ever seen,
Corporal Wittman?

00:58.068 --> 01:01.620
- Sir, yes, sir!
- [bleats]

01:04.586 --> 01:05.896
- You think you can do
whatever you want to

01:06.000 --> 01:08.724
while you're over here,
and maybe you can,

01:08.827 --> 01:10.448
but not while you're
on my base.

01:10.551 --> 01:12.689
While you're on my base,
you follow my orders.

01:12.793 --> 01:15.413
- Yes, Colonel.
- Damn right.

01:20.758 --> 01:22.344
You seem unhealthily attached
to this goat, Private.

01:22.448 --> 01:26.000
- Just didn't want
to see it killed, sir.

01:26.103 --> 01:27.965
[dramatic music]

01:28.068 --> 01:31.551
- Looks like it's been a while
since its last meal.

01:33.206 --> 01:34.724
But no animals on base.

01:34.827 --> 01:37.931
Feed it, give it some water,
get it the hell off.

01:38.034 --> 01:39.068
You hear me, Private?

01:39.172 --> 01:40.689
- Yes, sir.
- [bleats]

01:40.793 --> 01:47.758
♪

02:07.620 --> 02:08.103
- I'd like to speak
to him alone, please.

02:08.206 --> 02:10.758
- Yes, Ma'am!

02:16.413 --> 02:17.482
- Get up.

02:25.689 --> 02:28.620
You look very at home in here.

02:28.724 --> 02:31.344
- This place is actually bigger
than my CHU, Ma'am.

02:34.413 --> 02:35.827
- I need a favor.

02:35.931 --> 02:37.344
- There's not much I can do
from in here.

02:37.448 --> 02:38.310
- If you do this for me,

02:38.413 --> 02:39.413
I'll recommend that

02:39.517 --> 02:41.206
all the charges against you
get dropped.

02:41.310 --> 02:42.413
- What's the favor?

02:42.517 --> 02:43.931
- The LN you brought in
the other day

02:44.034 --> 02:46.620
left recovery in bad shape.

02:46.724 --> 02:48.000
If he doesn't get
brought back to me

02:48.103 --> 02:51.413
and put on a massive dose
of antibiotics, he's gonna die.

02:51.517 --> 02:52.482
- The good-lookin' kid?

02:52.586 --> 02:53.689
- His name is Qasem.

02:53.793 --> 02:56.206
He's my patient,
and I'm responsible for him.

02:56.310 --> 02:57.448
And you brought him in,

02:57.551 --> 03:00.000
so I'm assuming you might
know where to find him.

03:00.103 --> 03:02.862
- Do you mind if I ask you why
you're taking such an interest

03:02.965 --> 03:04.068
in this particular LN?

03:04.172 --> 03:04.965
- Sergeant!
- Yes, Ma'am!

03:05.068 --> 03:07.724
- I'm done with him.

03:07.827 --> 03:08.827
- No, wait, wait, wait!
Hey, hey, wait!

03:08.931 --> 03:13.379
I can find him
and I can bring him back.

03:13.482 --> 03:15.413
- Then do it.

03:15.517 --> 03:18.310
[suspenseful music]

03:18.413 --> 03:24.517
♪

03:27.000 --> 03:28.586
- I'm not sure about this.

03:28.689 --> 03:29.758
- This mission's keeping me
out of the brig,

03:29.862 --> 03:32.206
so I'd appreciate it
if you got sure about it.

03:32.310 --> 03:33.448
- Not like Holloway

03:33.551 --> 03:35.689
to stick her neck out like this
for an LN.

03:35.793 --> 03:36.965
- No.

03:37.068 --> 03:38.172
Makes you think
there's an actual human being

03:38.275 --> 03:39.172
under all that regular army.

03:39.275 --> 03:42.068
- Come on.
Cut her some slack.

03:42.172 --> 03:44.068
She chose putting up with all
your insubordinate bullshit

03:44.172 --> 03:46.586
over being with her family.

03:46.689 --> 03:49.137
- Can't wait
to see you two get married.

03:49.241 --> 03:50.241
- Wanna be my best man?

03:50.344 --> 03:51.379
- You get her a ring?

03:54.310 --> 03:56.275
- Shit.
I didn't think about that.

03:56.379 --> 03:57.689
- Give me an onion ring.
I don't care.

03:57.793 --> 04:00.448
- How romantic.

04:00.551 --> 04:02.655
- Guess instead of honeymooning
in Bora Bora,

04:02.758 --> 04:03.758
you guys'll be honeymooning
in Tora Bora.

04:03.862 --> 04:05.517
[laughs]

04:05.620 --> 04:07.000
- Laugh all you want.

04:07.103 --> 04:08.620
When we're married,

04:08.724 --> 04:10.137
we're entitled to
300 bucks a month

04:10.241 --> 04:13.379
extra housing allowance.

04:13.482 --> 04:16.517
- Marry me.
- [laughs]

04:16.620 --> 04:19.413
Let's get this over with.

04:19.517 --> 04:22.172
[upbeat music]

04:22.275 --> 04:27.206
♪

04:27.310 --> 04:29.172
- ♪ Somebody tell me to go

04:29.275 --> 04:32.551
♪

04:32.655 --> 04:33.689
♪ Somebody tell me to go

04:33.793 --> 04:37.241
♪

04:37.344 --> 04:40.586
♪ Somebody tell me to go

04:44.137 --> 04:44.758
- [bleats]

04:44.862 --> 04:48.172
- [chuckles]
Hey.

04:48.275 --> 04:49.310
How are ya?

04:51.965 --> 04:52.965
Mmm.

04:54.344 --> 04:57.551
Sir, I'm getting rid of it.

04:57.655 --> 05:01.137
- What becomes of this goat
makes no matter to me, Private.

05:01.241 --> 05:02.655
- Glad to hear that, sir.

05:02.758 --> 05:05.103
- However,
I am keenly interested

05:05.206 --> 05:06.137
in what happened
to an ambulance

05:06.241 --> 05:09.517
that disappeared
the other day.

05:09.620 --> 05:12.034
- Ambulance?
[stammers]

05:12.137 --> 05:14.068
I don't know anything
about that.

05:14.172 --> 05:15.310
- Oh, really?

05:15.413 --> 05:17.344
Because your name was
on the vehicle manifest.

05:18.034 --> 05:20.517
You seem nervous.

05:20.620 --> 05:21.965
- Oh, I'm--I'm fine, sir.

05:22.068 --> 05:24.586
- You're sweating profusely.
- It's hot, sir.

05:24.689 --> 05:25.793
- You're visibly shaking.

05:25.896 --> 05:29.379
- It's an unfortunate
medical condition, sir.

05:29.482 --> 05:31.310
- The truth, Private.

05:31.413 --> 05:33.965
- Okay.
Roback and Davis made me do it.

05:34.068 --> 05:35.931
They filled it
with expired medical supplies

05:36.034 --> 05:38.000
and took it to village to trade
with the warlords for hashish.

05:38.103 --> 05:39.275
- What?

05:39.379 --> 05:40.517
- Then the ambulance
got torched by SecCorp guys

05:40.620 --> 05:42.172
but we can't be sure,
so we stole one of their SUVs

05:42.275 --> 05:44.931
after the goat bit
off some guy's fingers

05:45.034 --> 05:48.965
and then hit a landmine
on the way back, sir.

05:49.068 --> 05:50.896
- I see.

05:51.000 --> 05:51.827
- [stammers]

05:51.931 --> 05:53.275
What are you gonna do
to me, sir?

05:53.379 --> 05:55.448
- [exhales deeply]
Nothing right now.

05:55.551 --> 05:58.551
It's Roback and Davis that
need to answer for this.

05:58.655 --> 05:59.517
- [bleats]

06:03.103 --> 06:05.862
[soft dramatic music]

06:05.965 --> 06:07.310
- [sighs]

06:07.413 --> 06:11.068
Well, Boz,
that was a close one.

06:11.172 --> 06:12.275
You hungry?

06:12.379 --> 06:16.103
♪

06:16.206 --> 06:19.551
[chickens clucking]

06:19.655 --> 06:21.620
- Where do we find Qasem?

06:21.724 --> 06:23.586
- Petrocelli said
he thought the little brother

06:23.689 --> 06:24.482
came from a house
with a green door.

06:27.344 --> 06:29.620
- What else did he say?

06:29.724 --> 06:31.689
- Nothing.
That was it.

06:31.793 --> 06:32.620
- Great.

06:32.724 --> 06:35.413
Time to play
green door roulette.

06:38.068 --> 06:39.896
- Let's start with that one.

06:42.068 --> 06:45.896
[tense music]

06:46.000 --> 06:52.344
♪

07:03.931 --> 07:05.241
- Clear!
- Clear!

07:05.344 --> 07:07.068
- Hallway!

07:07.172 --> 07:11.000
♪

07:11.103 --> 07:11.379
- All clear.

07:15.103 --> 07:16.517
- What now?

07:18.172 --> 07:20.034
- We hit every other green door
in the neighborhood.

07:20.137 --> 07:21.413
- And wait for everyone

07:21.517 --> 07:23.965
to just invite us in
for sponge cake and espresso?

07:24.068 --> 07:27.103
- Well there's nothing here,
so let's start knocking.

07:30.206 --> 07:31.793
- God damn.

07:35.827 --> 07:38.413
- What the fuck
are you doing?

07:38.517 --> 07:40.034
New way to get high?

07:40.137 --> 07:42.448
- Smells like burned hair.

07:42.551 --> 07:45.689
- This is a real motherfuckin'
silk rug.

07:45.793 --> 07:48.034
Worth 30 grand back home.
We're taking it.

07:48.137 --> 07:49.000
- I know you're in dire st--

07:49.103 --> 07:52.068
[suspenseful music]

07:52.172 --> 07:54.103
♪

07:54.206 --> 07:55.758
- Looks like an ISIS tunnel.

07:55.862 --> 07:58.793
♪

07:58.896 --> 08:00.275
- Let's just
take the rug and split.

08:00.379 --> 08:01.344
- We gotta go
down there.

08:01.448 --> 08:03.172
- I didn't sign up
for this.

08:03.275 --> 08:04.586
- Remember when you signed that
little piece of paper

08:04.689 --> 08:06.448
in the recruiting station?

08:06.551 --> 08:09.413
That was you signing up
for this.

08:09.517 --> 08:10.931
We're goin' in.

08:11.034 --> 08:12.965
♪

08:18.068 --> 08:19.689
[suspenseful music]

08:19.793 --> 08:26.000
♪

09:15.310 --> 09:17.344
- Next man!
- Coming in.

09:19.862 --> 09:21.896
- Coming in!

09:25.862 --> 09:26.965
- All clear.

09:27.068 --> 09:29.793
[soft dramatic music]

09:29.896 --> 09:35.448
♪

09:35.551 --> 09:37.689
- Who's this?
- My name is Azad.

09:37.793 --> 09:44.862
♪

09:51.034 --> 09:55.689
- He's the little brother.

10:04.310 --> 10:05.344
[knife clacks loudly]

10:06.172 --> 10:07.827
- Where's that fuckin' goat?

10:07.931 --> 10:09.172
- Uh--

10:09.275 --> 10:10.655
I have no idea.

10:10.758 --> 10:12.068
- Well, you damn well
better have some idea.

10:12.172 --> 10:13.344
- Look--even
if you cut it open,

10:13.448 --> 10:16.655
your fingers would be
totally digested by now.

10:16.758 --> 10:18.206
- Yeah, it's not my fingers
I'm looking for, mate.

10:18.310 --> 10:19.482
- Huh?

10:19.586 --> 10:21.068
- It's my Crimson Tide
championship ring

10:21.172 --> 10:22.344
that was on one
of those fingers.

10:22.448 --> 10:24.448
That's what I'm fuckin'
looking for.

10:24.551 --> 10:26.862
- Wait, you played football
for Alabama?

10:27.758 --> 10:29.103
- One more time:

10:29.206 --> 10:32.137
Where is that fucking goat?

10:32.241 --> 10:35.068
- I told you.
I don't know.

10:35.172 --> 10:36.482
- Yeah, you do,

10:36.586 --> 10:39.172
and if I don't get my finger
back with that ring on it,

10:39.275 --> 10:40.551
- [gasps]

10:40.655 --> 10:41.793
- I'm gonna take one of yours.

10:41.896 --> 10:43.827
- What?

10:44.655 --> 10:45.827
Ow.

10:46.896 --> 10:49.344
- You have one hour.

10:56.000 --> 10:58.448
- My brother was not well.

10:58.551 --> 11:01.413
He was having
great difficulty breathing.

11:01.517 --> 11:02.413
He became very weak.

11:02.517 --> 11:04.827
He finally had to leave me.

11:04.931 --> 11:06.206
- To go where?

11:06.310 --> 11:08.827
- He was told the warlord was
in possession of antibiotics.

11:08.931 --> 11:09.724
- Our antibiotics.

11:09.827 --> 11:12.103
- He has not returned.

11:12.206 --> 11:13.517
I am worried.

11:13.620 --> 11:14.758
- We're gonna get him
and we're gonna bring him back

11:14.862 --> 11:16.413
to the hospital at our base
to get better.

11:16.517 --> 11:18.413
- One of us is gonna need
to be here with the kid

11:18.517 --> 11:20.103
in case Qasem comes back.

11:20.206 --> 11:22.310
- You must
leave the woman here with me.

11:22.413 --> 11:24.275
The warlord will have no
interest in dealing with her.

11:24.379 --> 11:25.413
- "The woman"?

11:28.724 --> 11:30.206
- You're babysitting.
- No, no. Don't do this to me.

11:30.310 --> 11:32.310
- No, no.
It won't take long, okay?

11:32.413 --> 11:34.206
- Give you two a chance
to get close.

11:38.655 --> 11:41.586
- [scoffs]

11:44.793 --> 11:46.896
- Here, Boz.
Look.

11:47.000 --> 11:49.000
See, see?
Yeah.

11:49.103 --> 11:50.206
Come on.

11:50.310 --> 11:52.551
- [bleats]

11:52.655 --> 11:54.758
- What the hell are you doing?

11:54.862 --> 11:58.275
- I am trying to feed it
this horchata grip 'n rip.

11:58.379 --> 11:59.655
- Oh, that shit
gave me the runs.

11:59.758 --> 12:02.655
- Yeah?
Well, I am counting on it.

12:02.758 --> 12:04.241
Here, Boz.

12:04.344 --> 12:05.724
[smooches]
Up here.

12:05.827 --> 12:08.896
Here.
Come on, here.

12:09.000 --> 12:12.172
Yeah, okay.
Atta boy.

12:12.275 --> 12:13.275
There we go.

12:14.724 --> 12:15.724
- Yo, I meant it
about you being my best man.

12:15.827 --> 12:17.827
- No offense,

12:17.931 --> 12:20.793
but I kinda take this
marriage thing more seriously.

12:20.896 --> 12:21.896
- Is that a no?

12:22.000 --> 12:23.448
- It's not a no.

12:23.551 --> 12:26.344
Just kinda hoping you two would
take it more seriously, too.

12:26.448 --> 12:30.172
- Yeah, well.
I'm not Alvarez's type.

12:30.275 --> 12:31.862
- She tell you that?
- Every day.

12:31.965 --> 12:34.172
Besides, I'm not over Durkin.

12:34.275 --> 12:35.344
Unfortunately complicated

12:35.448 --> 12:36.586
by the fact
that she's totally over me.

12:36.689 --> 12:38.620
[horn honks]

12:38.724 --> 12:39.689
- A salaam alaikum!
God bless the USA!

12:39.793 --> 12:41.655
- Son of a bitch!

12:41.758 --> 12:43.620
- Looks like
those Afghan Army guys

12:43.724 --> 12:45.793
got that SecCorp SUV
running again.

12:45.896 --> 12:48.482
[engine revs]

12:48.586 --> 12:50.241
Damn!

12:50.344 --> 12:53.103
Those ANA guys can turn
anything into a technical.

12:53.206 --> 12:54.482
- We gotta track it down.

12:54.586 --> 12:55.862
- How exactly
are we gonna track it down?

12:55.965 --> 12:57.206
- There's a way.

12:57.310 --> 12:57.896
I just haven't thought
of it, yet.

12:58.000 --> 12:59.965
- You keep me posted.

13:00.068 --> 13:04.344
- Always the pessimist, amigo.

13:09.206 --> 13:10.103
No?

13:10.206 --> 13:11.862
- [speaking Pashto]

13:12.689 --> 13:14.275
- That's that.
- Hold on.

13:17.172 --> 13:19.689
- [speaking Pashto]
- Trade?

13:19.793 --> 13:22.586
- [speaking Pashto]

13:23.689 --> 13:24.965
- We don't have anything
to trade.

13:25.068 --> 13:27.068
- What do you got on you?
- What do you got on you?

13:27.172 --> 13:29.862
- Supplies and water.
- Me, too.

13:29.965 --> 13:30.862
- What about here?

13:30.965 --> 13:32.172
- Hey.
Hell, no.

13:32.275 --> 13:33.413
It's not gonna happen.

13:33.517 --> 13:35.344
- It's time to put away
childish things, amigo.

13:35.448 --> 13:37.344
Gimme your gamer.

13:40.241 --> 13:44.413
- I need
to at least wipe it first.

13:44.517 --> 13:46.275
I got personal stuff
on here.

13:46.379 --> 13:48.689
- Porn?
- Among other things.

13:48.793 --> 13:50.275
- Weird, fucked up porn?

13:50.379 --> 13:53.000
- Normal, everyday porn.

13:54.172 --> 13:57.448
- I'm sure warlords
could jerk off, too.

13:57.551 --> 13:58.344
Stop it.

14:01.551 --> 14:03.413
- [speaking Pashto]

14:03.517 --> 14:05.551
[video game music playing]

14:05.655 --> 14:06.896
- Come on.

14:07.000 --> 14:07.896
Now that you're happy,
let's try this one more time.

14:08.000 --> 14:10.310
- [speaking Pashto]

14:10.413 --> 14:12.206
- Paghman?
- Paghman.

14:12.310 --> 14:13.206
- He's at Paghman Hospital.

14:13.310 --> 14:15.689
- He's probably okay.
- Okay?

14:15.793 --> 14:16.793
What part of Paghman Hospital
do you not get?

14:16.896 --> 14:17.793
[speaking Pashto]

14:17.896 --> 14:20.310
- [speaking Pashto]

14:20.413 --> 14:22.310
Salaam alaikum!

14:22.413 --> 14:24.310
[suspenseful music]

14:24.413 --> 14:26.931
- You are not married?

14:27.034 --> 14:28.344
- Will be soon.

14:28.448 --> 14:29.689
- Is it arranged?

14:29.793 --> 14:32.000
- Sort of.

14:32.103 --> 14:33.965
- When you are married,
you will have children, yes?

14:34.068 --> 14:35.551
- I will have children?
No.

14:35.655 --> 14:37.275
- And your husband
allows this?

14:37.379 --> 14:39.000
- It's not up to him.

14:39.103 --> 14:39.689
- But he is the man.

14:39.793 --> 14:42.103
- I am the woman.

14:42.206 --> 14:43.862
- Why do you not want
to talk to me?

14:43.965 --> 14:45.965
Is it because I'm a man?

14:46.068 --> 14:47.000
- You're not a man!

14:47.103 --> 14:48.344
You're a boy.

14:48.448 --> 14:51.206
And it's because I find your
attitude very annoying.

14:51.310 --> 14:53.344
How lucky you for you
that you happen to be born

14:53.448 --> 14:55.103
with a little pee-pee
between those legs

14:55.206 --> 14:57.344
that lets you make
all the decisions

14:57.448 --> 14:58.275
for the women
in your culture.

15:01.413 --> 15:03.517
- You are very angry.

15:04.862 --> 15:06.551
- And believe it or not,

15:06.655 --> 15:09.793
you caught me on a good day.

15:09.896 --> 15:10.275
[punching bag thumping]

15:17.103 --> 15:19.000
- Kid's giving you the finger.

15:35.103 --> 15:36.379
- Ah, shit.

15:36.482 --> 15:38.655
- Notice he didn't ask
for his wedding ring back.

15:38.758 --> 15:41.137
- So we're all good?

15:41.241 --> 15:43.000
- You and me?

15:43.103 --> 15:45.000
Yeah, we're all good.

15:45.103 --> 15:45.827
But that fucking goat and me?

15:45.931 --> 15:47.896
Oh, we're far from good.

15:48.000 --> 15:50.862
- But you got your ring back.

15:50.965 --> 15:52.586
- Fingers are still missing.

15:52.689 --> 15:55.413
- Nothing the goat
can do about that.

15:55.517 --> 15:57.172
- Revenge is not about
remedying a situation,

15:57.275 --> 16:00.620
it's about eye
for a fuckin' eye.

16:00.724 --> 16:02.551
- You're gonna
take the goat's finger?

16:02.655 --> 16:04.103
- Didn't know goats
had fingers.

16:04.206 --> 16:05.517
- They have cloven hooves.

16:05.620 --> 16:06.413
- I'm not gonna take
the goat's fingers.

16:06.517 --> 16:08.448
I'm gonna take
the goat's life.

16:08.551 --> 16:09.620
And I know
it's on this base,

16:09.724 --> 16:11.827
and I'm gonna
fuckin' find it.

16:11.931 --> 16:13.034
- No, you're not.

16:13.137 --> 16:14.275
- Yeah.

16:15.448 --> 16:17.206
- Kid's not gonna give up
that goat without a fight.

16:17.310 --> 16:18.827
- Yeah, I'm gonna
find that fuckin' animal,

16:18.931 --> 16:20.965
and I'm gonna gut it like
the goddamn catch of the day.

16:27.758 --> 16:29.517
- He's a great poet.

16:29.620 --> 16:31.793
I know you do not read a lot,
but do not worry.

16:31.896 --> 16:34.241
These poems are short.

16:34.344 --> 16:36.689
A small child
could read them.

16:36.793 --> 16:39.206
- You really
can't help yourself, can you?

16:41.793 --> 16:42.793
- I was in the middle

16:42.896 --> 16:44.172
of my all-time high score
on that thing.

16:44.275 --> 16:48.000
- Well, maybe you should try
reading a book instead, amigo.

16:48.103 --> 16:49.655
- The engine
on the bird's running.

16:49.758 --> 16:50.482
Let's go.

16:50.586 --> 16:52.103
- You have found my brother?

16:52.206 --> 16:53.206
- He's at Paghman.
We're gonna go get him.

16:53.310 --> 16:55.827
[dramatic music]

16:55.931 --> 16:57.241
- Hey.

16:57.344 --> 16:58.344
Figured only one of you would
be alive when we got back.

16:58.448 --> 17:00.931
I had you, but Davis' money
was on the kid.

17:01.034 --> 17:03.103
- I'm never having children.

17:03.206 --> 17:04.206
Especially boys.

17:04.310 --> 17:06.827
- We'll discuss this
after we're married.

17:06.931 --> 17:09.827
[energetic music]

17:09.931 --> 17:13.482
♪

17:13.586 --> 17:16.482
[indistinct radio chatter]

17:16.586 --> 17:18.310
- Can't understand a thing.

17:18.413 --> 17:20.344
Can't tell if we've got
permission to land or not.

17:20.448 --> 17:22.620
Sounds like chaos down there.

17:22.724 --> 17:25.379
For better or worse,
we're going in.

17:25.482 --> 17:28.379
[screaming and crying]

17:28.482 --> 17:30.551
[suspenseful music]

17:30.655 --> 17:33.758
♪

17:33.862 --> 17:34.862
- You speak English?

17:34.965 --> 17:37.379
- Of course I do. I'm a doctor.
[indistinct]

17:37.482 --> 17:39.862
- What happened here?
- Suicide bombing at a wedding.

17:39.965 --> 17:45.551
♪

17:45.655 --> 17:48.068
- Look, we're looking
for a patient called Qasem.

17:48.172 --> 17:49.896
Do you have anybody here
by that name?

17:50.000 --> 17:51.379
- You are kidding me, right?

17:51.482 --> 17:53.206
You are welcome
to go look for him yourself,

17:53.310 --> 17:54.655
but I have no idea where he is,

17:54.758 --> 17:56.379
nor do I have the time
to worry about him.

17:56.482 --> 17:58.793
- Is there anything
we can do here to help?

17:58.896 --> 18:00.965
- You can find this person
you're looking for

18:01.068 --> 18:03.862
and take him away so I have
one less person to deal with.

18:03.965 --> 18:09.482
♪

18:09.586 --> 18:10.931
- [indistinct speech]
Shh, shh.

18:11.034 --> 18:12.344
[prays softly]

18:12.448 --> 18:15.241
- Let's limit our boots
on the ground time here, okay?

18:15.344 --> 18:16.206
- For sure.

18:16.310 --> 18:23.344
♪

18:45.793 --> 18:48.206
- That him?

18:48.310 --> 18:50.689
- If it is,
our work here is done.

18:50.793 --> 18:54.172
♪

18:54.275 --> 18:55.862
- I got him!

18:55.965 --> 19:01.241
Hey, can you hear me?
Hey.

19:01.344 --> 19:01.931
- You again.

19:02.034 --> 19:04.931
- Okay, shit.

19:05.034 --> 19:07.103
♪

19:07.206 --> 19:09.034
Okay.
Hey.

19:09.137 --> 19:10.517
We're gonna get you
out of here, okay?

19:10.620 --> 19:17.448
♪

19:19.586 --> 19:21.620
Door!

19:23.413 --> 19:25.206
We managed
to stabilize him on the bird,

19:25.310 --> 19:26.517
but he's still
in pretty bad shape.

19:26.620 --> 19:28.793
- I'll take it
from here, Sergeant.

19:32.896 --> 19:34.000
Who's this?

19:34.103 --> 19:35.551
- His little brother.
They're a package deal.

19:35.655 --> 19:37.931
- Get that kid
and all of his germs

19:38.034 --> 19:39.103
out of my operating room,
please!

19:39.206 --> 19:40.103
Thank you.

19:40.206 --> 19:41.827
- Let's get him on the table!

19:41.931 --> 19:47.586
♪

19:47.689 --> 19:49.034
- How'd you take care
of yourself

19:49.137 --> 19:51.724
while your brother was away?

19:51.827 --> 19:53.620
- Relatives would feed me.

19:53.724 --> 19:56.172
And since the killing of my
parents shut down the school,

19:56.275 --> 19:58.931
I was no longer a target.

19:59.034 --> 19:59.793
- You seem
to accept your misfortunes

19:59.896 --> 20:03.448
so much better than I do.

20:03.551 --> 20:07.034
- We do not expect everything
to turn out well like you do,

20:07.137 --> 20:08.620
so we're never disappointed.

20:08.724 --> 20:12.620
♪

20:12.724 --> 20:13.379
- Hmm.

20:13.482 --> 20:15.862
- Gimme a sec, hon.

20:15.965 --> 20:18.413
We were reading about another
one of those suicide bombings.

20:18.517 --> 20:21.034
The boys are getting worried
about you,

20:21.137 --> 20:22.379
but I told them
you were miles away

20:22.482 --> 20:23.103
from where that stuff
happens.

20:23.206 --> 20:25.103
- And they believed you?

20:25.206 --> 20:27.137
- Well, it doesn't really
matter, does it?

20:27.241 --> 20:28.551
- Is that Mom?
- Yeah, it's Mom.

20:28.655 --> 20:30.379
- Hi.

20:30.482 --> 20:32.896
- Hi, Mom!
We miss you.

20:33.000 --> 20:34.344
Don't get blown up.

20:34.448 --> 20:36.931
- Don't be an idiot.
She's totally safe.

20:37.034 --> 20:39.241
- I am.
I'm totally safe.

20:39.344 --> 20:40.275
- That shirt is dirty.
I told you not to wear it.

20:40.379 --> 20:41.655
Now we're gonna be late
to school.

20:41.758 --> 20:43.551
Change that, please.
Is Rufus locked out again?

20:43.655 --> 20:46.724
I told you you gotta
let him in after he pees.

20:46.827 --> 20:47.827
It's out of control here.

20:47.931 --> 20:48.965
I love you.
Can I call you tomorrow?

20:49.068 --> 20:52.448
Okay, bye.
[computer beeps]

20:53.758 --> 20:55.241
- [sighs]

20:55.689 --> 20:56.448
- Hi.

20:56.551 --> 20:58.413
- Hey.

20:59.827 --> 21:00.724
- You okay?

21:00.827 --> 21:01.793
- Mm, yeah.

21:01.896 --> 21:03.896
Just missing
the peace and quiet of home.

21:04.000 --> 21:05.517
[chuckles]
What's up?

21:05.620 --> 21:07.551
- I head you sprung Roback
from the brig.

21:07.655 --> 21:09.344
Mind if I ask why?

21:09.448 --> 21:11.275
- Between you and me?

21:11.379 --> 21:13.793
He did me a solid.

21:13.896 --> 21:14.931
- Well, the reason I ask

21:15.034 --> 21:17.137
is that he's suddenly
on my radar,

21:17.241 --> 21:18.241
so I need to know if we
consider him friend or foe.

21:18.344 --> 21:23.275
- At this specific moment
in time, friend.

21:23.379 --> 21:25.206
But I'm sure that'll change
in an hour.

21:25.310 --> 21:28.448
- [chuckles]
That's all I needed to know.

21:33.517 --> 21:35.586
[soft dramatic music]

21:35.689 --> 21:43.551
♪

21:56.275 --> 21:58.379
- You were right.

21:58.482 --> 22:02.413
I was not ready to leave.

22:02.517 --> 22:05.758
It is possible you may know
more about medicine that I do.

22:05.862 --> 22:08.482
- [chuckles softly]

22:08.586 --> 22:15.448
♪

22:16.034 --> 22:18.241
[distant explosions]

22:31.068 --> 22:33.103
- Why do you find
the destruction

22:33.206 --> 22:37.620
of confiscated weapons
and explosives entertaining?

22:37.724 --> 22:40.000
Do you not get enough
of this horror in battle?

22:40.103 --> 22:44.448
- You have a way
of really killing fun.

22:46.137 --> 22:49.310
- It is a privilege
to be allowed

22:49.413 --> 22:51.310
to be out amongst men at night.

22:51.413 --> 22:54.724
I do not think
that you appreciate it.

22:54.827 --> 22:57.172
- Don't consider it a perk.

22:57.275 --> 23:01.931
- Your culture takes all
of these things for granted.

23:02.034 --> 23:04.758
In my culture,

23:04.862 --> 23:10.000
a mother is expected only
to bring a son into the family.

23:10.103 --> 23:12.517
- How can a woman
even survive here?

23:12.620 --> 23:15.000
♪

23:15.103 --> 23:19.931
- She can be raised as a boy.

23:20.034 --> 23:24.413
- What do you mean?

23:24.517 --> 23:27.931
- In my culture, some parents
can make the decision

23:28.034 --> 23:32.862
to raise their daughters
as sons.

23:32.965 --> 23:35.758
That way we are allowed
to have interactions with men,

23:35.862 --> 23:39.620
allowed to have jobs,

23:39.724 --> 23:42.862
allowed to
leave the house at night.

23:48.103 --> 23:50.275
- Oh, my God.

23:54.551 --> 23:56.689
You're a girl?

24:03.172 --> 24:04.793
- It is true.

24:04.896 --> 24:06.862
I was born female.

24:06.965 --> 24:09.344
- Do you feel like a boy?

24:10.724 --> 24:14.482
- I feel like
Allah has blessed me,

24:14.586 --> 24:17.896
that I was chosen
to have a chance in life.

24:18.000 --> 24:21.172
- What happens
when you get older?

24:21.275 --> 24:25.793
- Life becomes much more
difficult and dangerous.

24:25.896 --> 24:28.655
- You mean
if someone finds out?

24:28.758 --> 24:29.793
- It is not a question
of if they find out,

24:29.896 --> 24:33.068
but rather if they approve.

24:33.172 --> 24:35.586
- Well,
it's gonna be pretty difficult

24:35.689 --> 24:37.517
to keep your little secret
on this base.

24:37.620 --> 24:39.448
- Why?

24:39.551 --> 24:41.758
- Well, you're gonna have to
shower at some point,

24:41.862 --> 24:43.000
and I'm for sure

24:43.103 --> 24:43.793
not letting you do it
with the men on this base.

24:43.896 --> 24:46.172
- Then I will not shower.

24:46.275 --> 24:48.724
- [groans quietly]
You'll have to sleep somewhere.

24:48.827 --> 24:51.586
[soft dramatic music]

24:51.689 --> 24:54.275
Unless you want me
to take you back home.

24:54.379 --> 24:57.620
- I will never
leave my brother again.

24:57.724 --> 24:59.931
- Then you're gonna have to

25:00.034 --> 25:04.689
share your little secret
with others.

25:04.793 --> 25:09.068
- [sighs]

25:09.172 --> 25:14.000
- I'm sorry that I got a
bit annoyed with you before.

25:14.103 --> 25:16.689
Your male privilege was

25:16.793 --> 25:18.793
really pissing me off.

25:18.896 --> 25:20.896
- [chuckles]

25:21.000 --> 25:24.379
- You're very good
at being a boy.

25:24.482 --> 25:27.517
- It is a lot easier
than it looks.

25:27.620 --> 25:29.827
[laughter]

25:31.137 --> 25:33.137
- The closest ANA base
is here.

25:33.241 --> 25:34.758
- What if they aren't
stationed at the base?

25:34.862 --> 25:37.482
What if they're floaters
just passing through?

25:37.586 --> 25:38.551
- Well, then
we'll never track down the SUV,

25:38.655 --> 25:40.655
there'll be no fight,
and we're screwed.

25:40.758 --> 25:43.172
- Forget I mentioned it.

25:43.275 --> 25:44.758
- If I can just
figure out a way to--

25:44.862 --> 25:46.206
- Gentlemen.

25:46.310 --> 25:48.724
both: Sir.
- [chuckles]

25:50.448 --> 25:55.275
Oh, I had an interesting little
talk with Private Petrocelli.

25:55.379 --> 25:57.000
- He's a good kid.
- Great kid.

25:57.103 --> 25:58.655
- Yes, the young lad
told me all about

25:58.758 --> 26:01.620
your eventful nocturnal jaunt
through the countryside

26:01.724 --> 26:03.068
the other night.

26:03.172 --> 26:04.724
- Oh, shit.
- The kid likes to embellish.

26:04.827 --> 26:06.931
- Oh, the tale he told me
needs no embellishment.

26:07.034 --> 26:11.000
It is a tale
of sneaking off base

26:11.103 --> 26:15.310
to trade expired medicines
for hashish to a local warlord

26:15.413 --> 26:17.000
and then

26:17.103 --> 26:18.034
burning a military ambulance.

26:18.137 --> 26:19.517
- We're not
the ones who torched it.

26:19.620 --> 26:21.586
- Oh, yes.

26:21.689 --> 26:23.068
The private was quite clear
on that point.

26:23.172 --> 26:24.103
- Sir, those meds were
designated to be destroyed.

26:24.206 --> 26:25.172
- Or traded for ten pounds

26:25.275 --> 26:27.448
of grade A Afghan hashish,
it seems.

26:27.551 --> 26:28.965
- The village
needed them badly.

26:29.068 --> 26:31.896
- Oh, you two are quite
the humanitarians, aren't you?

26:32.000 --> 26:34.724
- And they were still
perfectly good.

26:34.827 --> 26:36.000
- You don't have to tell me.

26:36.103 --> 26:38.517
I hate how big pharma

26:38.620 --> 26:40.034
invents these expiration dates
simply to make more money

26:40.137 --> 26:42.689
by inducing earlier churn
on supplies.

26:42.793 --> 26:43.862
It's shameful.

26:43.965 --> 26:45.275
- It is shameful.
- Pisses us off, too.

26:45.379 --> 26:47.896
- However, demanding hashish
in return for those drugs?

26:48.000 --> 26:50.758
Mm--[clicks tongue]
is also shameful.

26:50.862 --> 26:52.241
- We feel bad, sir.

26:52.344 --> 26:54.103
- Oh, I'm sure you do.

26:56.137 --> 26:57.137
[chuckles]

26:57.241 --> 27:00.586
Look, I like you both,
all right?

27:00.689 --> 27:02.068
You're damn good medics.

27:02.172 --> 27:04.137
And between us,

27:04.241 --> 27:05.689
I have been known to imbibe

27:05.793 --> 27:07.758
on the local Afghan hashish
myself, occasionally.

27:07.862 --> 27:09.275
- It is primo.

27:09.379 --> 27:10.793
- Be that as it may,

27:10.896 --> 27:13.137
I'm ordering you to destroy
everything you have.

27:13.241 --> 27:14.655
All ten pounds of it,

27:14.758 --> 27:17.793
because if I hear that you are
selling it around the base,

27:17.896 --> 27:20.758
and I will hear about it,

27:20.862 --> 27:23.103
I'll recommend that you both
be court-martialed.

27:23.206 --> 27:24.482
- Yes, sir.

27:26.379 --> 27:29.655
- Oh,
and about that ambulance--

27:29.758 --> 27:31.137
both: Yes, sir?

27:31.241 --> 27:35.793
- That is property
of the United States Army.

27:40.586 --> 27:42.620
But I'm British Forces,
so screw it.

27:50.862 --> 27:53.551
- We can't destroy the hashish.
It's all we got.

27:53.655 --> 27:55.517
- We may not have to.

27:57.034 --> 27:57.482
- Hoo!

27:57.586 --> 28:00.241
Lovely.

28:00.344 --> 28:01.931
What'd you blokes want from me?

28:02.034 --> 28:02.931
- We need you
to turn it all into edibles

28:03.034 --> 28:05.034
so it'll be easier
to hide and move.

28:05.137 --> 28:07.551
- I have the technology.
- Fantastic.

28:07.655 --> 28:09.551
- For 50%.

28:09.655 --> 28:10.931
- Fuck that.

28:11.034 --> 28:13.310
- I'm supposed to do this out
of the kindness of my heart?

28:13.413 --> 28:15.551
- We were thinking you would
take it as collateral

28:15.655 --> 28:17.034
for the Sasquatch fight.

28:17.137 --> 28:19.000
- So I bloody well
am supposed to do this

28:19.103 --> 28:20.172
out of the kindness
of my heart.

28:20.275 --> 28:22.482
- This fight is gonna be big.

28:22.586 --> 28:25.034
You can stand
to make a shitload of book.

28:25.137 --> 28:25.724
- You got Sasquatch
to agree to it?

28:25.827 --> 28:27.551
- We're working on it.

28:27.655 --> 28:29.413
- Then this whole
conversation's

28:29.517 --> 28:30.551
just taking place in a dream.

28:30.655 --> 28:32.379
- How 'bout this?

28:32.482 --> 28:33.689
If the fight doesn't happen,

28:33.793 --> 28:34.931
you can keep half of it
as payment for the last fight.

28:35.034 --> 28:37.379
- Here's an even better deal.

28:37.482 --> 28:39.896
If the fight doesn't happen,
I keep the whole bloody thing.

28:40.000 --> 28:41.551
- You just said 50%.

28:41.655 --> 28:43.172
- Prices fluctuate.

28:45.793 --> 28:46.724
- Okay, fine.

28:46.827 --> 28:49.379
Agreed.

28:49.482 --> 28:52.137
- About this fight, mate.
- Yeah?

28:52.241 --> 28:54.034
- I'm gonna want
to check out your man.

28:54.137 --> 28:56.379
Make sure he's up to the task
so I can put out decent odds.

28:56.482 --> 28:59.551
I'm not agreeing to anything
until I lay eyes on your boy.

28:59.655 --> 29:00.517
- Of course.

29:00.620 --> 29:02.931
- And I am not
gonna be the one

29:03.034 --> 29:04.517
to convince Sasquatch
to fight him.

29:04.620 --> 29:05.517
You blokes are.

29:05.620 --> 29:07.000
- Not gonna be a problem.
- Good.

29:07.103 --> 29:09.206
Now get the hell out
of my kitchen

29:09.310 --> 29:11.310
so I can turn this hash
into food.

29:11.413 --> 29:13.310
- Think you should
disguise it as MREs.

29:13.413 --> 29:16.931
Nobody touches those.
It'll be safer.

29:17.034 --> 29:18.379
- So you know exactly
where they are

29:18.482 --> 29:20.551
and you could just
steal 'em back from me?

29:20.655 --> 29:24.275
Do I look like a fuckin' idiot
to you, mate?

29:24.379 --> 29:25.275
Oh, by the way, mate.

29:25.379 --> 29:29.000
It's chicken.
All week long.

29:29.103 --> 29:30.482
[cackles]

29:30.586 --> 29:33.827
[helicopters blades whirring]

29:33.931 --> 29:35.896
- [chuckles]

29:36.000 --> 29:38.793
You got a little
Corporal Buckley in you.

29:38.896 --> 29:40.551
You know that?

29:42.586 --> 29:44.758
[sighs]

29:44.862 --> 29:48.586
You know, he was
the coolest dude I ever met.

29:48.689 --> 29:50.965
He knew the origin story

29:51.068 --> 29:54.172
of every Marvel character
by heart.

29:54.275 --> 29:56.551
Even the ones nobody knew.

29:56.655 --> 29:59.413
And he didn't let anyone
fuck with me.

29:59.517 --> 30:02.000
I'm not gonna let anyone
fuck with you,

30:02.103 --> 30:05.655
but I can't hide you
in here forever.

30:05.758 --> 30:09.379
[soft dramatic music]

30:09.482 --> 30:11.413
We're gonna get through this.

30:11.517 --> 30:19.379
♪

30:25.103 --> 30:29.000
- I got a ton of forms
for you and Roback to sign.

30:29.103 --> 30:30.862
- For what?

30:30.965 --> 30:33.379
- For the marriage?

30:33.482 --> 30:35.068
- Oh, yeah.

30:38.172 --> 30:43.103
- You're really not
into Roback, huh?

30:43.206 --> 30:44.689
- What exactly
did he tell you?

30:44.793 --> 30:46.034
- Look, don't worry.

30:46.137 --> 30:47.172
I'm not gonna tell anyone.

30:47.275 --> 30:49.862
- Sorry if I fucked up
everything with him.

30:49.965 --> 30:50.586
- [chuckles]

30:50.689 --> 30:53.655
- Sasquatch seems

30:53.758 --> 30:54.827
big.

